<div id="train" class="tab active">
<div class="travel-wrapper">
<div class="row">
<div class="columnx2-left-travel">

    <h2>Train </h2>
    <p>A direct service operates between London Paddington and Oxford Station approximately every 30 minutes with a journey time of around one hour. University College is around one mile from the station, a fairly short, straightforward walk, although taxis are also available at the station.
    </p>
    <p>The last train from Oxford station back to London is at around 23:00. Details of train times and online ticket purchase can be found at <a href="https://www.thetrainline.com" target="_blank">thetrainline.com</a>.
    </p>
    <p> Trains also run between Birmingham New Street and Oxford. Other services operate from the North via Birmingham New Street; from the South via Reading; and from the West via Didcot or Reading.
    </p>
</div>
