<div id="car" class="tab">
<div class="travel-wrapper">
<div class="row">
<div class="columnx2-left-travel">
    <h2>Car</h2>
    <p>Many Oxford streets are closed to traffic and parking is severely limited. </p>
    <p>  If you are staying in accommodation in Oxford then it may offer parking for guests. Otherwise, if you would like to come by car, we encourage you to use the <a href="https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/roads-and-transport/public-transport/park-and-ride/locations" target="_blank">Park and Ride</a> bus services. </p>
    <p> These operate between the city centre and parking areas on the outskirts. There are five <a href="https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/roads-and-transport/public-transport/park-and-ride/locations" target="_blank">Park and Ride sites</a> which serve Oxford City Centre. </p>
    <p>
    <ul>
    <li>Oxford Parkway (north). For satnav use OX2 8HA.  Take the 500 bus to and from the city centre. </li>
    <li>Pear Tree (north). For satnav use OX2 8JD.  Take the 300 bus to and from the city centre. </li>
    <li>Redbridge (south). For satnav use OX1 4XG.  Take the 300 bus to and from the city centre. </li>
    <li>Thornhill (east). For satnav use OX3 8DP.  Take the 400 bus to and from the city centre. </li>
    <li>Seacourt (west). For satnav use OX2 0HP.  Take the 400 bus to and from the city centre. </li>
    </ul>
    </p>
    <p> <a href="https://www.oxford.gov.uk/directory_record/354/thornhill_park_and_ride/category/56/park_and_ride_sites" target="_blank">Thornhill Park and Ride </a> is the site that is easiest to reach from London. The journey time for getting from the Park and Ride sites to the centre of the city is around 15 minutes. </p>
    <p>The car park is accessible 24 hours a day but buses stop running at around 19:15 from the town centre on Saturdays. Timetables are available <a href="https://parkandride.oxfordbus.co.uk/timetables/" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>
    <p> Car parks are also available in the city centre. Oxford City Council recommends using <a href="https://www.oxford.gov.uk/directory_record/344/oxpens_car_park/category/53/city_centre_car_parks" target="_blank"> Oxpens car park </a> if you are driving into the city centre. More details can be found <a href="https://www.oxford.gov.uk/directory/8/car_parks_in_oxford/category/53" target="_blank">here</a>.


</div>
